   "text": "Every gate is a SET comparison, never a count. A rising row count does not prove continuity.",
   "fontSize": 11.5,
   "fontFamily": 2,
   "textAlign": "left",
   "verticalAlign": "top",
   "containerId": null,
   "originalText": "Every gate is a SET comparison, never a count. A rising row count does not prove continuity.",
   "lineHeight": 1.25
  },
  {
   "angle": 0,
   "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
   "fillStyle": "solid",
   "strokeWidth": 1,
   "strokeStyle": "solid",
   "roughness": 1,
   "opacity": 100,
   "groupIds": [],
   "frameId": null,
   "version": 1,
   "isDeleted": false,
   "boundElements": [],
   "updated": 1,
   "link": null,
   "locked": false,
   "id": "f1",
   "type": "text",
   "x": 60,
   "y": 815,
   "width": 445.50000000000006,
   "height": 18.75,
   "backgroundColor": "transparent",
   "roundness": null,
   "seed": 489728228,
   "versionNonce": 1581781472,
   "text": "THE SIX DECISIONS THIS WHOLE DIAGRAM EXISTS TO SUPPORT",
   "fontSize": 15,
   "fontFamily": 1,
   "textAlign": "left",
   "verticalAlign": "top",
   "containerId": null,
   "originalText": "THE SIX DECISIONS THIS WHOLE DIAGRAM EXISTS TO SUPPORT",
   "lineHeight": 1.25
  },
  {
   "angle": 0,
   "strokeColor": "#343a40",
   "fillStyle": "solid",
   "strokeWidth": 1,
   "strokeStyle": "solid",
   "roughness": 1,
   "opacity": 100,
   "groupIds": [],
   "frameId": null,
   "version": 1,
   "isDeleted": false,
   "boundElements": [],
   "updated": 1,
   "link": null,
   "locked": false,
   "id": "f2",
   "type": "text",
   "x": 60,
   "y": 845,
   "width": 936.6500000000001,
   "height": 97.5,
   "backgroundColor": "transparent",
   "roundness": null,
   "seed": 1763531147,
   "versionNonce": 523753355,
   "text": "1  TradeEvent, not the Buy instruction \u2014 instruction is intent, event is the fill; prices slip between them\n2  PumpSwap pools need RPC \u2014 the event names a pool, not a coin; that fact was set in the past, the stream only carries the present\n3  'Failed' lives on the transaction, not the event \u2014 transactions are all-or-nothing; only the tx knows the verdict\n4  RPC inside process() is a bug \u2014 it blocks the one-at-a-time hot path and Carbon silently drops the overflow\n5  Capture RAW wire bytes, not decoded events \u2014 a fixture holding your own output tests your file-reader, not your decoder\n6  Identity = signature + absolute_path + event_ordinal \u2014 (signature, instruction_index) collides on CPI-nested fills",
   "fontSize": 13,
   "fontFamily": 2,
   "textAlign": "left",
   "verticalAlign": "top",
   "containerId": null,
   "originalText": "1  TradeEvent, not the Buy instruction \u2014 instruction is intent, event is the fill; prices slip between them\n2  PumpSwap pools need RPC \u2014 the event names a pool, not a coin; that fact was set in the past, the stream only carries the present\n3  'Failed' lives on the transaction, not the event \u2014 transactions are all-or-nothing; only the tx knows the verdict\n4  RPC inside process() is a bug \u2014 it blocks the one-at-a-time hot path and Carbon silently drops the overflow\n5  Capture RAW wire bytes, not decoded events \u2014 a fixture holding your own output tests your file-reader, not your decoder\n6  Identity = signature + absolute_path + event_ordinal \u2014 (signature, instruction_index) collides on CPI-nested fills",
   "lineHeight": 1.25
  },
  {
   "angle": 0,
   "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
   "fillStyle": "solid",
   "strokeWidth": 1,
   "strokeStyle": "solid",
   "roughness": 1,
   "opacity": 100,
